Decentralized Energy Trading L1
Overview

Decentralized Energy Trading L1 is a blockchain infrastructure designed to facilitate peer-to-peer energy markets. It enables households, businesses, and renewable energy producers to trade electricity directly without centralized intermediaries.

Features

Peer-to-peer energy trading

Tokenized energy credits

Smart contract settlement

Renewable energy verification

Transparent pricing mechanisms

Architecture
Energy Registry

Stores verified records of energy production and consumption.

Trading Engine

Matches buyers and sellers in decentralized markets.

Settlement Layer

Handles automated payments through smart contracts.

Monitoring Layer

Tracks energy generation and grid interactions.

Use Cases

Solar energy marketplaces

Local microgrid trading

Renewable energy credit markets

Smart city energy infrastructure
